There's this Asian store that I pass by whenever I can and a lot of local high school girls into anime and kpop hang out there, and I'm pretty sure I contribute to making the place feel less LARPy for them because I always just buy bottles of alcohol instead of like pocky sticks.

Like all the girls are getting the cute meme products and bringing manga to read there together and stuff like that meanwhile I am just getting the rice wine and cooking ingredients, to me it's just a real store instead of a cultural club thing. I am just an average Joe customer.

Was talking to an ob gyn doctor a few weeks ago and she mentioned that in her clinical experience those women who don't monitor their pregnancy, don't do doctor's appointments and ultrasounds etc. and just give birth one day always have some of the healthiest babies w/ no issues.

She thought it was a paradox but it's obviously just selection bias because to be this irresponsible you have to usually be in your early 20s and free of any symptoms or chronic illnesses yourself... But goes to show most people are way too neurotic about health things like this.
